commands.name: /advancement
commands.description: Gives, removes, or checks player advancements.

commands.name: /attribute
commands.description: Queries, adds, removes or sets an entity attribute.

commands.name: /clone
commands.description: Copies blocks from one place to another.

commands.name: /damage
commands.description: Applies damage to the specified entities.

commands.name: /data
commands.description: Gets, merges, modifies, and removes block entity, entity, and command storage NBT data.

commands.name: /debug
commands.description: Starts or stops a debugging session.

commands.name: /deop
commands.description: Revokes operator status from a player.

commands.name: /enchant
commands.description: Adds an enchantment to a player's selected item.

commands.name: /experience
commands.description: An alias of /xp. Adds or removes player experience.

commands.name: /fill
commands.description: Fills a region with a specific block.

commands.name: /fillbiome
commands.description: Fills a region with a specific biome.

commands.name: /forceload
commands.description: Forces chunks to constantly be loaded or not.

commands.name: /gamerule
commands.description: Sets or queries a game rule value.

commands.name: /give
commands.description: Gives an item to a player.

commands.name: /jfr
commands.description: Starts or stops a JFR profiling.

commands.name: /kick
commands.description: Kicks a player off a server.

commands.name: /locate
commands.description: Locates closest structure, biome, or point of interest.

commands.name: /loot
commands.description: Drops items from an inventory slot onto the ground.

commands.name: /me
commands.description: Displays a message about the sender.

commands.name: /msg
commands.description: An alias of /tell and /w. Displays a private message to other players.

commands.name: /op
commands.description: Grants operator status to a player.

commands.name: /perf
commands.description: Captures info and metrics about the game for 10 seconds.

commands.name: /place
commands.description: Used to place a configured feature, jigsaw, template, or structure at a given location.

commands.name: /publish
commands.description: Opens single-player world to local network.

commands.name: /random
commands.description: Draw a random value or control the random number sequence.

commands.name: /reload
commands.description: Reloads loot tables, advancements, and functions from disk.

commands.name: /return
commands.description: Control execution flow inside functions and change their return value.

commands.name: /ride
commands.description: Used to make entities ride other entities, or stop entities from riding.

commands.name: /rotate
commands.description: Changes the rotation of an entity.

commands.name: /say
commands.description: Displays a message to multiple players.

commands.name: /schedule
commands.description: Delays the execution of a function.

commands.name: /setblock
commands.description: Changes a block to another block.

commands.name: /setidletimeout
commands.description: Sets the time before idle players are kicked.

commands.name: /spawnpoint
commands.description: Sets the spawn point for a player.

commands.name: /spectate
commands.description: Make one player in spectator mode spectate an entity.

commands.name: /teammsg
commands.description: An alias of /tm. Specifies the message to send to team.

commands.name: /tellraw
commands.description: Displays a JSON message to players.

commands.name: /tick
commands.description: Controls the tick rate of the game.

commands.name: /time
commands.description: Changes or queries the world's game time.

commands.name: /transfer
commands.description: Triggers a transfer of a player to another server.

commands.name: /trigger
commands.description: Sets a trigger to be activated.

commands.name: /waypoint
commands.description: Manages waypoints displayed on the locator bar.
